Description: Floor sherd, with top of foot, of Attic black-glazed pottery stemless cup; remains of slight ring foot; two plastic ridges on underside; wholly glazed; impressed decoration on interior: two zones of tongues with maeander between; inscription cut on underside.
Curator's comments: For the impressed pattern with two zones of tongues, compare Athens, Agora P 9201 (Agora xii, pl. 51 no. 500); for the underside, compare Athens, Agora P 5332 (Agora xii, pl. 23 no. 484).
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.34)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1557)
